# Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file content to Netlify Dashboard → Site Settings → Environment variables

# ===================================================================
# NeonDB Database Connection
# ===================================================================
# Get this from NeonDB Dashboard → Connection Details
# Format: postgresql://username:password@host/database?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://your-username:your-password@ep-xxx.region.neon.tech/your-database?sslmode=require

# ===================================================================
# Instructions
# ===================================================================
# 1. Go to https://app.netlify.com
# 2. Select your site
# 3. Go to Site settings → Environment variables
# 4. Click "Add a variable"
# 5. Key: DATABASE_URL
# 6. Value: <paste your connection string from NeonDB>
# 7. Scopes: Check both "Build" and "Functions"
# 8. Click "Create variable"
# 9. Redeploy your site to apply changes

